":"frog","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"frog(1x)"},"G957":{"id":"G957","lemma":"βελτίον","translit":"beltíon","derivation":"neuter of a compound of a derivative of G906 (βάλλω) (used for the comparative of G18 (ἀγαθός));","strongs_def":"better","kjv_def":"very well"},"G906":{"id":"G906","lemma":"βάλλω","translit":"bállō","derivation":"a primary verb;","strongs_def":"to throw (in various applications, more or less violent or intense)","kjv_def":"arise, cast (out), X dung, lay, lie, pour, put (up), send, strike, throw (down), thrust","pos":"verb","usage":"cast(86x), put(13x), thrust(5x), lay(3x), lie(2x)"},"G914":{"id":"G914","lemma":"Βαραχίας","translit":"Barachías","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H01296);","strongs_def":"Barachias (i.e. Berechijah), an Israelite","kjv_def":"Barachias","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Barachias(1x)"},"G907":{"id":"G907","lemma":"βαπτίζω","translit":"baptízō","derivation":"from a derivative of G911 (βάπτω);","strongs_def":"to immerse, submerge; to make whelmed (i.e. fully wet); used only (in the New Testament) of ceremonial ablution, especially (technically) of the ordinance of Christian baptism","kjv_def":"Baptist, baptize, wash","pos":"verb","usage":"wash(2x), baptist(1x)"},"G931":{"id":"G931","lemma":"βάσανος","translit":"básanos","derivation":"perhaps remotely from the same as G939 (βάσις) (through the notion of going to the bottom);","strongs_def":"a touch-stone, i.e. (by analogy) torture","kjv_def":"torment","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"torment(3x)"},"G903":{"id":"G903","lemma":"Βαλαάμ","translit":"Balaám","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H01109);","strongs_def":"Balaam, a Mesopotamian (symbolic of a false teacher)","kjv_def":"Balaam","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Balaam(3x)"},"G919":{"id":"G919","lemma":"Βαριησοῦς","translit":"Bariēsoûs","derivation":"of Chaldee origin (H01247 and H03091);","strongs_def":"son of Jesus (or Joshua); Bar-jesus, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Barjesus"},"G990":{"id":"G990","lemma":"βλέμμα","translit":"blémma","derivation":"from G991 (βλέπω);","strongs_def":"vision (properly concrete; by implication, abstract)","kjv_def":"seeing"},"G916":{"id":"G916","lemma":"βαρέω","translit":"baréō","derivation":"from G926 (βαρύς);","strongs_def":"to weigh down (figuratively)","kjv_def":"burden, charge, heavy, press","pos":"verb"},"G955":{"id":"G955","lemma":"Βελίαλ","translit":"Belíal","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H01100);","strongs_def":"worthlessness; Belial, as an epithet of Satan","kjv_def":"Belial"},"G978":{"id":"G978","lemma":"Βιθυνία","translit":"Bithynía","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Bithynia, a region of Asia","kjv_def":"Bithynia","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Bithynia(2x)"},"G966":{"id":"G966","lemma":"Βηθσαϊδά","translit":"Bēthsaïdá","derivation":"of Chaldee origin (compare H01004 and H06719);","strongs_def":"fishing-house; Bethsaida, a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Bethsaida","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Bethsaida(7x)"},"G912":{"id":"G912","lemma":"Βαραββᾶς","translit":"Barabbâs","derivation":"of Chaldee origin (H01347 and H05);","strongs_def":"son of Abba; Bar-abbas, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Barabbas","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Barabbas(11x)"},"G970":{"id":"G970","lemma":"βία","translit":"bía","derivation":"probably akin to G979 (βίος) (through the idea of vital activity);","strongs_def":"force","kjv_def":"violence","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"violence(4x)"},"G962":{"id":"G962","lemma":"Βηθαβαρά","translit":"Bēthabará","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H01004 and H05679);","strongs_def":"ferry-house; Bethabara (i.e. Bethabarah), a place on the Jordan","kjv_def":"Bethabara","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Bethabara(1x)"},"G977":{"id":"G977","lemma":"βιβρώσκω","translit":"bibrṓskō","derivation":"a reduplicated and prolonged form of an obsolete primary verb (perhaps causative of G1006 (βόσκω));","strongs_def":"to eat","kjv_def":"eat"},"G934":{"id":"G934","lemma":"βασίλειος","translit":"b